==English==
===Etymology===
Latin ''Phosphorus'', Greek [[Φωσφόρος]] (from [[φωσ]] [fôs] - light, and [[φερω]] [pherô] - to bring), ''Phôsphoros'', the bearer of light. 

===Pronunciation===
*(''[[RP]]''): fŏs'fərəs, /ˈfɒsfərəs/, /<tt>"fQsf@r@s</tt>/
*(''US''): fäs'fərəs, /ˈfɑsfɚəs/, /<tt>"fAsf@`@s</tt>/

===Homophones===
*[[phosphorous]], [[phosphorus]]

===Proper noun===
'''Phosphorus''' (or '''Phosphor''')
[[Category:English nouns]]

#a name sometimes used for [[Hesperus]], the [[personification]] in Greek [[mythology]] of the planet [[Venus]].
#an ancient Greek name for the [[Morning Star]] (the planet Venus when it is visible in the sky before [[sunrise]]).

